The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 London, July 24: Oil fell more than $23 a barrel from its record peak of above $147 on July 11, marking the biggest fall in dollar term since futures began trading in New York in 1983. In percentage terms, the 15 percent tumble is the steepest pull-back since early 2007. U.S. light crude fell as low as $123.62 a barrel, the lowest since early June.                             
	 Mumbai, July 24: Market watchdog Sebi has said mutual funds will have to prepare their schemewise annual reports according to a new format, produced by it in consultation with apex mutual fund association, AMFI.                            
	 Mumbai, July 24: Pantaloon Retail (India) Ltd has declared a bonus issue of shares with differential voting rights to the existing shareholders. The new shares will entitle the shareholders to an additional 5 per cent dividend over the regular dividend.                            
	 New Delhi, July 24: ONGC has won a legal battle in Australia entitling it to claim Rs 100 crore as performance bank guarantee from Clough Engineering with which it had a commercial dispute over unfinished development of deep-sea blocks in KG-basin.                            
	 New Delhi, July 24: Tax payers can deposit income tax from the bank accounts of any person in addition to credit and debit cards, the CBDT has said.                                                                                                                         
